    {
      "id": "lBze5dtsUHxDoPkQaTzYp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 6875.54037966752,
      "y": 639.388716127431,
      "width": 1195.708740234375,
      "height": 233.33333333333297,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 151943613,
      "version": 284,
      "versionNonce": 1426791037,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771927695896,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Think of any activity done by a person, it is a skill.\n\nEven this excalidraw chart creation is a skill that I \nhave learnt after a lot of practice",
      "fontSize": 46.66666666666659,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Think of any activity done by a person, it is a skill.\n\nEven this excalidraw chart creation is a skill that I \nhave learnt after a lot of practice",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "AD_v1zHyEqe8xty-tad8T",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 6929.426182890177,
      "y": 906.0551793435766,
      "width": 1091.0037841796875,
      "height": 233.33333333333297,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1l",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 832200509,
      "version": 568,
      "versionNonce": 1800629981,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771927787827,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The file is stored as json, so the model can be \nasked to create a chart for any topics. It can\nalso be given the prose, and made to show the \npictorial representation",
      "fontSize": 46.66666666666659,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The file is stored as json, so the model can be \nasked to create a chart for any topics. It can\nalso be given the prose, and made to show the \npictorial representation",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "y1PrEVTX2uJ2NqFkY2VdK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 8193.622337166706,
      "y": 634.944203866146,
      "width": 996.3306884765625,
      "height": 524.9999999999992,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1m",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1918966685,
      "version": 1134,
      "versionNonce": 621934589,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771928025687,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The skills are shell scripts written \nin plain english. \nSomething complicated as installing torch\non a system will require a deterministic \nscript. After that getting the system \nready for development, like creating folders,\nmanaging the environments, writing the \nimplementation plan, breaking it down into \ntasks. These can be converted to skills",
      "fontSize": 46.66666666666659,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The skills are shell scripts written \nin plain english. \nSomething complicated as installing torch\non a system will require a deterministic \nscript. After that getting the system \nready for development, like creating folders,\nmanaging the environments, writing the \nimplementation plan, breaking it down into \ntasks. These can be converted to skills",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "MlBW0uwPpFbYU7OafgUYY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4912.761076253043,
      "y": 706.5078405853797,
      "width": 1394.2001953125,
      "height": 2078.999999999997,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1n",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 889859775,
      "version": 2398,
      "versionNonce": 477502741,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771997970629,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 - AI models are calling the functions or tools more \naccurately\n\n2- Models can now edit more accurately, and do it at \nthe location that we are asking for\n\n3- Models have the workflow knowledge of non-coding \ndomain as well.\n\n4- With such knowledge they can build application ground\nup with less guidance from humans\n\n5- IDEs are having agents, which are prompts, tools with \nmodels. By nature the models are designed to just give\na single completion. To keep iterating in loop until the \n\"percieved\" output is reached, the agents have to be coded.\n\n6- Since Agents can be default while loop, they can be \nmade to do work that is like a todo list.\n\n7- It feels like the Agents are trained to complete what the \nprompt has asked it to complete. \n\nI suspect there is a mechanism in the AI model training, or \nthe probability of end token arriving only after the task \nis complete. [Nope, I was wrong, it is just going to give stop token]\n\nChecked with gemini, and found the AI Agent frameworks ship \nwith internal while loop, that keeps the Agent calling the LLM \nuntil the task is finished\n\nThe loop is broken if there is \"Final Answer\" in the LLM response.\n",
      "fontSize": 46.66666666666659,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 - AI models are calling the functions or tools more \naccurately\n\n2- Models can now edit more accurately, and do it at \nthe location that we are asking for\n\n3- Models have the workflow knowledge of non-coding \ndomain as well.\n\n4- With such knowledge they can build application ground\nup with less guidance from humans\n\n5- IDEs are having agents, which are prompts, tools with \nmodels. By nature the models are designed to just give\na single completion. To keep iterating in loop until the \n\"percieved\" output is reached, the agents have to be coded.\n\n6- Since Agents can be default while loop, they can be \nmade to do work that is like a todo list.\n\n7- It feels like the Agents are trained to complete what the \nprompt has asked it to complete. \n\nI suspect there is a mechanism in the AI model training, or \nthe probability of end token arriving only after the task \nis complete. [Nope, I was wrong, it is just going to give stop token]\n\nChecked with gemini, and found the AI Agent frameworks ship \nwith internal while loop, that keeps the Agent calling the LLM \nuntil the task is finished\n\nThe loop is broken if there is \"Final Answer\" in the LLM response.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "HTMZv4ktsJoeaEfMdu-MM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 6462.239408772571,
      "y": 1329.4998827635802,
      "width": 1140.7863866412472,
      "height": 146.00000000000014,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1o",
